ng in his rental car, two gang members began shooting into the area where Antonio was parked.  While his vehicle was still running, Antonio was shot once in the back of the head and died instantly while sitting in the driver's side of the vehicle.  His body was found a few hours later.  I had to bury my 36 year old husband who had just began working on his Ph.D in Education.  While in court, I was able to come face to face with both the murderers and the guns that were used during the shooting.  One was a semi-automatic rifle that stood just as tall as me.  Neither of the guns were registered to the then suspects who were eventually convicted of Antonio's murder.  They both received life sentences without parole.  However, that brings me nor my kids any relief.  It's horrible to watch your kids live in fear and cry as they have to live in the house we worked so hard for them to grow up in.  My daughter had to walk the hallway and pass the classroom where her dad taught everyday.  It hurt me to the core to watch her anguish about missing her dad.  My son is now 10 and still wants to know why his dad was in that &quot;box&quot; at church.  A huge piece of beauty was stolen from us 5 years ago.  I hope that the little light I've just shared with you will make a difference because my family, Team Coleman, deserves a vote.   -  Sesily   <\/p>\n<\/div><nav class=\"sharing\">\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"facebook\">\n            <div class=\"fb-like\" data-href=\"http:\/\/www.barackobama.com\/stories\/gun-violence\/20140\/\" data-ref=\"fb_like_btn\" data-send=\"false\" data-layout=\"button_count\" data-width=\"100\" data-show-faces=\"false\"><\/div>\n        <\/li>\n        <li class=\"twitter\">\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/share\" class=\"twitter-share-button\" data-text=\"Read Sesily C.'s story about Gun Violence, then read more from Obama supporters all over.\" data-url=\"http:\/\/www.barackobama.com\/stories\/gun-violence\/20140\/?source=tweet_btn\"